cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is about natural language generation in dialogue systems, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of recurrent neural networks and encoder-decoder framework suggests that it also belongs to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of pretrained models, which is a common technique in neural networks and deep learning, further supporting the inclusion of cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the improvement in grammar and naturalness of generated sentences, which could be considered a sub-topic of software engineering (cs.SD) related to natural language processing.
